\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

parity exchange
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 operation 
\begin_inset Formula $x\leftrightarrow y$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 being the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

time inversion
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 operator 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau\leftrightarrow\tau^{-1}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The two-sided lattice may be studied either as a lattice model, or as a
 dynamical system with time evolution given by 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau$
\end_inset

.
 It is interesting to juxtapose these two viewpoints.
